    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-07-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-07-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="457"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d457">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 15778/80.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Squiers</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-07-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 28, 1909</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Squiers reports that the Government of Panama agrees to demands of the United
                    States in the <hi rend="italic">Columbia</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Buffalo</hi>
                    cases. Says an indemnity of $5,000 will be paid in the <hi rend="italic"
                        >Columbia</hi> case; offers to pay $8,000 indemnity to the relatives of Rand
                    and $1,000 to Cieslik in the <hi rend="italic">Buffalo</hi> cases, and will
                    dismiss, by presidential decree, all police officers who were present at time of
                    disturbance in case of <hi rend="italic">Buffalo</hi>. Asks instructions.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
